---

## 🔍 Key Insights

- Elderly patients (70–80 age group) have the highest readmission rates.
- Emergency admissions are associated with increased readmission risk.
- Circulatory diseases contribute significantly to patient readmissions.
- Longer hospital stays are linked to higher chances of readmission.
- Patients requiring more medications generally represent higher-risk cases.
- Medication changes alone do not significantly reduce readmission rates.
- Internal Medicine and Emergency departments handle the majority of readmitted patients.

---

## 💡 Recommendations

- Strengthen post-discharge follow-up for elderly patients.
- Improve discharge planning for emergency admissions.
- Develop specialized care programs for high-risk diagnosis categories.
- Enhance medication adherence and patient education.
- Implement predictive monitoring systems for early readmission detection.

---

## 📈 Project Outcome
This project successfully identifies the major factors influencing diabetes patient readmission and demonstrates how data analytics can support healthcare organizations in making informed, data-driven decisions.

